<content type="str">The Defend Trade Secret Act contains a whistleblower immunity provision which could have a significant impact on employers. Until last month, however, no court had interpreted this provision which provides that no one &quot;shall be held criminally or civilly liable under Federal or State trade secret law for the disclosure of a trade secret&quot; made in confidence to a government official or an attorney and &quot;solely for the purpose of reporting or investigating a suspected violation of law.&quot; 
 
